-- Canadian Pacific, Union Fail to Reach Agreement, Railways Says
-- B y   C h r i s   D o n v i l l e
-- 2012-05-27T21:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-27/canadian-pacific-union-fail-to-reach-agreement-railways-says.html
  Canadian Pacific  Railway Ltd. and
union negotiators have ended labor talks without reaching an
agreement, setting the stage for Canada’s federal government to
end a five-day strike, a company spokesman said.  “The talks have ended and the legislative process, as I
understand it, will now commence,” CP spokesman Ed Greenberg
said today in a telephone interview with the Canadian
Broadcasting Corp.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
